<br>
This sort of attitude cracks me up.  Before T rods and focus items I went on some ToV raids where pretty much all I did was follow the crowd around and click on a nuke now and then.  Oh, how exciting.  Hey, folks barely knew I was there but oh, golly, I got to do a few K worth of damage on each mob.  Whoopee.<br>
<br>
Now when I go on ToV raids with my guild I'm pretty busy.  And appreciated.  It's always hectic at the beginning summoning focus items and resist gear.  But I have the satisfaction of knowing I increased the damage output of the raid and helped keep injuries down from AEs.  I keep our clerics supplied with T rods but they're good at what they do and they only need a few rods now and then.  I'm still able to throw some nukes around.  And mala and/or malosini if we're short on shamans.  And yes, I CoH latecomers...but they're my friends and they appreciate it.<br>
<br>
A lot of peeps can nuke.  But only mages can CoH, make others more efficient at spellcasting and keep clerics supplied with fast mana via T rods.  My friends appreciate what I can do, and they return the favor by helping me obtain the spells and gear I need.<br>
<br>
I'm not a masochist.  I'm a well adjusted individual who has learned to play nice with others.  If my guild treated me like a CoH slut I'd be a masochist.  But I'd never belong to a stupid guild like that. <p>Shazar Oom <BR>
Arch Mage <BR>
